# Dynamics 365 email rules

Follow `docs/D365_EMAIL_GUIDELINES.md` when creating or changing email modules.

- Treat a Dynamics test send as authoritative; browser previews are not enough.
- Use presentation tables and inline critical styles/HTML attributes.
- Use Dynamics `tbContainer multi`, `columnContainer`, and `data-container`
  metadata only for genuine editable layout columns.
- Keep headers, footers, nested buttons, and data tables free of Dynamics
  designer-column hooks.
- Ensure desktop fallbacks remain readable when mobile media queries are ignored.
- Build buttons from table cells and visible anchors. Do not hide anchors in
  non-MSO conditionals. The export strips `data-editorblocktype="Button"` so
  Dynamics cannot flatten the table into a background-less anchor.
- Never use the inline `background:` shorthand — Dynamics expands it to
  `background-image:initial…` and drops the color. Use `background-color` only.
- Do not combine an explicit `width:100%` anchor with horizontal padding where
  Outlook may ignore `box-sizing`.
- Give fixed images matching HTML and inline widths plus alt text.
- Keep Send Preview, Copy HTML, and CLI build output on the same hardening path.
- Verify the Send preview with **No media CSS** enabled; critical containment
  and alignment must not depend on responsive media queries.
- Run `npm test` and `npm run build` after email markup or CSS changes.
- Add an assertion to `scripts/audit-email.js` for every rendering regression.
